(243, 1, '2010-09-30 10:53:05', '2010-09-30 10:53:05', 'Today I had the chance to meet the recently formed creative collective, The <a href=\"http://www.hiddendingbat.co.uk/\">Hidden Dingbat</a>. Consisting of  the creative skills of Phil Howell and Lauren Baker two  graduates of  Colchester Institute. We started the workshop with a quick presentation, explaining how they had come to form the collective and their design education background. They then went on describe some of the trials and tribulations of the 3rd year and the problems that we can expect to encounter.\r\n\r\nSome of the main points;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Social networking - Get your self known.</li>\r\n	<li>Visit London - D&amp;AD lectures, exhibitions etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Make the most of Colchester - 15 Queen Street, Minories, Slat Space</li>\r\n	<li>Be nice, be positive</li>\r\n	<li>Be generous with your time and ideas</li>\r\n	<li>Speak to practitioners</li>\r\n	<li>PDP Like there is no tomorrow</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe rest of the work shop was based around the idea of creating brands for start up company trying to capitalise on the empty shops left by the recession. My brief was to design a logo for \'Kidz corner\'. I think the main things I took away from the workshop was the need to act proactively in my self promotion work, and really make the most of all the opportunities that we have this year.', 'Hidden Dingbats', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hidden-dingbats', '', '', '2010-12-07 11:49:06', '2010-12-07 11:49:06', '', 0, 'http://www.adroot.co.uk/journal/?p=243', 0, 'post', '', 0),
