(125, 1, '2010-01-15 23:24:34', '2010-01-15 23:24:34', 'This is just a quick update on my logo development. After much consideration and a lot of indecision I have come to the conclusion that my new identity for the Truman Brewery needs a strong mark. I have tried to capitalise on the quality of the type face I am using. I was hoping that just the pure fact of writing the name of the gallery in the font that is gill, would be enough to fill the mind of the viewer, (Consciously or unconsciously) with connotations of all things british. but unfortunately, for a number of reasons, (mainly the stipulation in the brief that I must create a logo) that the design is lacking.\r\n\r\nMy alternative is to introduce a mark which is instantly recognisable that I can use in a more subtle way to embed the brand of the gallery on different aspects of the brief.  I have settled with the silhouette of a water-lily. It is my best attempt so far to marry the british and asian cultures of the local area. I am still undecided on a colour, for the time being I will replicate the logo in all 5 of the colours used.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/01/lotus_colour2.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-123\" src=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/01/lotus_colour2.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"132\" /></a>', 'Logo Development', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '125', '', '', '2010-10-25 15:33:01', '2010-10-25 15:33:01', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/2010/01/15/125/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(130, 1, '2010-02-01 19:51:15', '2010-02-01 19:51:15', 'Again it has been to long between posts but as a quick update this is the latest version of my poster design. the brief for the design is a A3 poster which folds down to A5 size. The front must promote an event from one of the months listing. In this case the showing of the film \'The Krays\' at the \'Old Trumen\' (new name by the way) the back must be a list of the full months events. I\'ve tried to stick to the same colour palate as list before using the pink for the cinema events. See the link below for a look.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/02/a3_poster_slim2.pdf\">A3_Poster_Slim2</a>', 'The Poster', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-poster', '', '', '2010-10-25 15:32:49', '2010-10-25 15:32:49', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/2010/02/01/the-poster/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(224, 1, '2010-10-14 12:48:38', '2010-10-14 12:48:38', 'Today is my first post of the third year. The summer has been a exciting time for me, I managed to gain some work experience with Moneycorp, which proved be very productive. A design I had been working while in knightsbridge has been chosen for use in the airport. All though the initial brief was only for an A3 poster the final print is well over two metres (pictures to follow).\n\nI have also been working hard on my research for my FMP and dissertation. After much deliberation I think I have settled on a subject and for the most part a title. I have been spending a lot of time research information design, mapping and infographics, with particular reference to the internet. I feel this subject best sums up my career aspirations and should hopefully give me a platform in which to display my skills. I hope that due to the nature of the work and it\'s reliance on a large number of graphic applications, such as typography grid layouts ect, that it will accommodate most of the areas I am interested.\n\nIn the third year so far there has been a lot of talk specialising in a particular discipline. The main thinking behind this is that it can dramatically improves your chances of employment, If you focus all your efforts in one field, potentially you are a stronger candidate for a particular role as a posed to a \'Jack of all trades\' designer which can turn their hands to most tasks but is a master of none. The point I take difference to is that because a designer can work with image placement, grids, typography, illustration and web design etc that they do not have a area specialty. Unfortunately my argument fell apart because I could not find a role which satisfied most of these skills,This was until I found information design.', 'Summer Update', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '206-revision', '', '', '2010-10-14 12:48:38', '2010-10-14 12:48:38', '', 206, 'http://www.adroot.co.uk/journal/2010/10/14/206-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(138, 1, '2010-02-08 16:19:09', '2010-02-08 16:19:09', 'After a very hectic week, my main project for semester one is finished and handed in! I just wanted to post the digital versions of the final pieces. Pack Shoots of the physicals copies will have to come at a later date.\n\n<a href=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/02/a3_poster_cinema.pdf\">A3_Poster_Cinema</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/02/a3_poster_commerce.pdf\">A3_Poster_Commerce</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/02/a3_poster_fblock.pdf\">A3_Poster_FBLOCK</a>', 'Old Truman', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'old-truman', '', '', '2010-02-08 16:19:09', '2010-02-08 16:19:09', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/2010/02/08/old-truman/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(199, 1, '2010-02-12 04:56:28', '2010-02-12 04:56:28', 'Old Truman Evaluation\r\n\r\nOverall I have been very pleased with my progress on the main project for semester one. The real guts of the project was to try and get a sense of what brick lane was then and what is now. And Ultimately translate that into a coherent brand. I tried to stay with a very clean set of designs because I wanted to steer away from the temptations of over complicating the final work with grunge textures and backgrounds. I think that its was a good progression for me too, Mainly because it was a lot harder to make something like sophisticated than to make it look trendy. I think this move can really summaries the direction that my design focus has been moving in for the last couple of months.\r\n\r\nI have been trying to concentrate on the benefits of using grids systems when flowing text into document in indesign.  As well as some of the more technical aspects of typography. One of my biggest achievements I feel is that I have come up with a unique way of presenting the folding poster. By using a slim design and aligning the text I have achieved legibility on both surfaces when closed. (As apposed to the writing being upside down) I Was also very pleased with the colour palette I used through out the project. I think that this was one of the strongest elements of the the brand identity\r\n\r\nAreas where I could have improved through out the project was my ability to record my progression as I went along. I found myself spending hours in front of the computer tweaking designs without properly recording the development. I think that this could be detrimental to my final grade as it is a key aspect of the design process.', 'Old Truman Evaluation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'old-truman-evaluation', '', '', '2010-10-25 15:32:37', '2010-10-25 15:32:37', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/?p=199', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(143, 1, '2010-02-19 16:38:18', '2010-02-19 16:38:18', 'Just as a way of capping the last semesters terrible blog keeping, I am posting my first and last post on the take away seafood packaging support module. Here is the final  pack shoot of the packaging.\n\n<a href=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/02/packshot.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-144 alignleft\" src=\"http://adroot.files.wordpress.com/2010/02/packshot.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" /></a>', 'Takeaway Packaging', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'takeaway-packaging', '', '', '2010-02-19 16:38:18', '2010-02-19 16:38:18', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/?p=143', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(147, 1, '2010-02-19 17:12:51', '2010-02-19 17:12:51', '<strong>Confirmation of Graphic Media Practice.</strong>\r\n\r\nStarting how I mean to carry on, this is the brief for my main project in semester two.\r\n\r\n<strong>Great Speeches of the 20th century</strong>\r\n\r\nThe guardian newspaper brought together a collection of the greatest speeches of the twentieth Century. Each booklet contains an historical address and coverage of the speech from the time. The speeches are introduced by prominent figures ranging from FW de Klerck on Nelson Manuela\'s statement to the Rivonia trial to Mikhail Gorbachev on Nikitat Kruschev’s denunciation of Stalin.\r\n\r\nThe Brief: You are to select a minimum of three speeches. Consider the format that a ‘container of information’ can be; a book, booklet/pamphlet, broadsheet, pocket book, 3D object, artist-book, or photo book etc. Your design solutions could be combine illustration and/or your own/sourced photographs with the text, or it could be purely typographical or purely image based solution. Your design must work across the total collection of fourteen speeches. You are also to design the package/container/wrapper for all fourteen speeches (therefore you will need to make blind dummies for the whole series) these ‘books’ would be sold as a total collection in a selected shops such as the TATE or they may be designed as one off pieces.\r\n\r\nThis project is designed to allow you to develop your strengths and personal interests. If your passion is photography let the project be led by image, if your passion is typography let the project be led by text. If your passion is for craft, let the project be led by the handmade, and so on. Your exploration of ideas should be exciting, stimulating and test the conventions of normally excepted formats\r\n\r\nAddition research in 3 key areas will be helpful:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Content: the time frame in which the speeches was written, the speaker, the country of origin, social/cultural/political context.</li>\r\n	<li>Physical structure: formats, materials, textures and processes.</li>\r\n	<li>Working processes: technical application relating to typography, print specification, illustration, photography, 3D structures.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Speeches</strong>\r\n\r\nWinston Churchill\r\n<strong><em>We shall fight on the beaches </em></strong>\r\nThis is the edited text of the speech delivered to House of Commons on June 4 1940.\r\n\r\nJohn F Kennedy\r\n<strong><em>Ask not what your country can do for you </em></strong>\r\nThis speech was delivered by Kennedy at his presidential inauguration on January 20 1961.\r\n\r\nNelson Mandela\r\n<strong><em>An ideal for which I am prepared to die </em></strong>\r\nThis is the full text of Mandela\'s statement from the dock at the opening of his trial on charges of sabotage, supreme court of South Africa, Pretoria, April 20 1964.\r\n\r\nHarold Macmillan\r\n<strong><em>No going back </em></strong>\r\nDouglas Hurd: In South Africa, Macmillan delivered one of the defining statements of British policy in the 20th century.\r\n\r\nFranklin D Roosevelt\r\n<strong><em>The only thing we have to fear is fear itself</em></strong>\r\nThis speech was delivered by Roosevelt at his inauguration in Washington on March 4 1933.\r\n\r\nNikita Khrushchev\r\n<strong><em>The cult of the individual</em></strong>\r\nThis is an edited version of a speech delivered by Khrushchev to the 20th congress of the Communist party of the USSR in Moscow on February 25 1956.\r\n\r\nEmmeline Pankhurst\r\n<strong><em>Freedom or death </em></strong>\r\nThis is an edited version of a speech delivered by Pankhurst in Hartford, Connecticut on November 13 1913.\r\n\r\nMartin Luther King\r\n<strong><em>I have a dream </em></strong>\r\nThis speech was delivered by King on August 28 1963 at the Lincoln Memorial, Washington.\r\n\r\nCharles de Gaulle\r\n<strong><em>The flame of French resistance </em></strong>\r\nThese speeches were delivered by Charles de Gaulle and broadcast by the BBC in 1940.\r\n\r\nMargaret Thatcher\r\n<strong><em>The lady\'s not for turning </em></strong>\r\nThis speech was delivered to the Conservative party conference in Brighton on October 10 1980.\r\n\r\nJawaharlal Nehru\r\n<strong><em>A Tryst with Destiny\r\n</em></strong>This speech was delivered by Nehru to the Constituent Assembly of India in New Delhi on August 14 1947.\r\n\r\nVirginia Woolf\r\n<strong><em>Shakespeare\'s sister </em></strong>\r\nVersions of this speech were delivered by Woolf at Girton and Newnham colleges, University of Cambridge, on October 20 &amp; 26 1928.\r\n\r\nAneurin Bevan\r\n<strong><em>Weapons for squalid and trivial ends </em></strong>\r\nThis is an edited version of a speech delivered by Bevan to the House of Commons on December 5 1956.\r\n\r\nEarl Spencer\r\n<strong><em>The most hunted person of the modern age </em></strong>\r\nThis speech was delivered at the funeral of Diana, Princess of Wales, at Westminster Abbey on September 6 1997.', 'Great Speeches of the 20th Century', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'great-speeches-of-the-20th-century', '', '', '2010-10-25 15:31:40', '2010-10-25 15:31:40', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/?p=147', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(202, 1, '2010-02-21 05:36:00', '2010-02-21 05:36:00', 'I found this Project particularly difficult to get into, and unfortunately we did not have much time. Because of the way the studio sessions where set up, we where only given the brief in the second half of the semester. This made it particular hard to fit in the necessary studio sessions. Despite these problems I feel that I learnt a lot about studio photography. We had a range of taught studio sessions as well as the opportunity to try it on our own.\r\n\r\nIt think one thing that I achieved in this project was the uniformity and branding of the products. I tried to make the products look very natural together and to keep a constant design running throughout. I did also try to experiment with the design of the the box but settled with a variation of a classic style.\r\n\r\nSome of the aspects I found hard about the brief was actually constructing the boxes them selves. For a support module I felt that there was a lo of work involved. Because of the nature of the products the boxes had to a least a certain size so it was hard and expensive to have the graphics printed onto a sheet of paper big enough to accommodate the large net. There was also the added issues of double sided printing as well as the weight of the paper need to maintain the structure of the box. Over all I think one of the biggest lesson I have learnt from this brief is the ability to problem solve. For all the problems above a quick and cost effective solution had to be found. I hope that my final product reflect how this was achieved.', 'Takeaway Packaging Evaluation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'takeaway-packaging-evaluation', '', '', '2010-10-25 15:31:54', '2010-10-25 15:31:54', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/?p=202', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(150, 1, '2010-03-03 11:43:52', '2010-03-03 11:43:52', 'Last week we was set the project of redesigning the artwork for one our favourite albums of the last decade. After much deliberation I chose the an album by Mark Ronson. The Song was a cover of a Maximo Park called \"<em>Apply Some Pressure</em>\" and even features the lead singer. I think I chose this song more because of the lyrics rather than anything else. Especially as when the album was released they had a particular meaning to me. A week after the project we all met up to show our work and get some feedback on what we had done, I am relatively pleased with he final out even if it isn\'t as polished as I would like it to be (being a one day project). The overall feed back was positive although there was some mention of a certain \" clinical\" style i seem to have  adopted so that is defiantly something to look out for in the future.\r\n\r\nSo Here is the Front Cover\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.adroot.co.uk/journal/files/2010/03/album_cover2.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-154 alignleft\" src=\"http://www.adroot.co.uk/journal/files/2010/03/album_cover2.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>', 'One Day Project', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'one-day-project', '', '', '2010-10-25 15:31:25', '2010-10-25 15:31:25', '', 0, 'http://adroot.wordpress.com/?p=150', 0, 'post', '', 0),
