(206, 1, '2010-09-14 12:48:38', '2010-09-14 12:48:38', 'Today is my first post of the third year. The summer has been a exciting time for me, I managed to gain some work experience with Moneycorp, which proved be very productive. A design I had been working while in knightsbridge has been chosen for use in the airport. All though the initial brief was only for an A3 poster the final print is well over two metres (pictures to follow).\r\n\r\nI have also been working hard on my research for my FMP and dissertation. After much deliberation I think I have settled on a subject and for the most part a title. I have been spending a lot of time research information design, mapping and infographics, with particular reference to the internet. I feel this subject best sums up my career aspirations and should hopefully give me a platform in which to display my skills. I hope that due to the nature of the work and it\'s reliance on a large number of graphic applications, such as typography grid layouts ect, that it will accommodate most of the areas I am interested.\r\n\r\nIn the third year so far there has been a lot of talk specialising in a particular discipline. The main thinking behind this is that it can dramatically improves your chances of employment, If you focus all your efforts in one field, potentially you are a stronger candidate for a particular role as a posed to a \'Jack of all trades\' designer which can turn their hands to most tasks but is a master of none. The point I take difference to is that because a designer can work with image placement, grids, typography, illustration and web design etc that they do not have a area specialty. Unfortunately my argument fell apart because I could not find a role which satisfied most of these skills,This was until I found information design.', 'Summer Update', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'summer-update', '', '', '2010-12-07 11:49:35', '2010-12-07 11:49:35', '', 0, 'https://adroot.wordpress.com/2010/10/14/summer-update/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
