(231, 1, '2010-03-25 22:55:06', '2010-03-25 22:55:06', 'Today we had a lecture from a previous student of the institute. He came to speak to us about the work he does now at seymourpowell and what he had to do to get there. Laurence Willmot graduated in 2007 and has been since working at seymourpowel. Although there was a lot of work he could not speak to us about due to the time scales involved in the projects,( The final idea may not some to fruition for several years) It was very interesting to me to find out how the design process works in such a big  company, and how there different departments work together. We were also lucky enough to get Lawrence on our own for a while to talk to him about his experiences as a student and what he done to get a job after graduating. There where 3 main points that stuck out to me;\n\n1. Enter Competitions - The more you enter the more experience you get, and the more chance you have of being successful. Laurence entered his final major project from University into a number of competitions and got a lot of positive feedback.\n\n2. Work Placements - Ultimately Laurence got the job as a result of a successful work placement over the space of two years.\n\n3. Online Portfolio - <a href=\"http://www.insightoutsight.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">insightoutsight</a> is the name of the online collaboration Laurence is involved in. It consists of a number of his uni friends which come together to display there personal work.', 'Seymourpowell', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '194-revision', '', '', '2010-03-25 22:55:06', '2010-03-25 22:55:06', '', 194, 'http://www.adroot.co.uk/journal/2010/03/25/194-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
