(384, 1, '2011-06-30 10:00:26', '2011-06-30 10:00:26', 'For my FMP project I have created a fictional element of the NHS called myHealth. myHealth would be tasked with promoting and making accessible, patients individual data and medical history.\r\n\r\nOne of the key influences of the project was the work of American designer and writer Thomas Goetz. Goetz’s work revolves around ‘engaging people in their health and involving them as decision makers’, which he believes results in improved health as a consequence. The myHealth project is an extension of this idea.\r\n\r\nUnlike many of the recent health campaigns that focus on the negative effects of neglecting your health, the main premise of myHealth is that patients will react in a more proactive and responsible way when given clear positive reinforcement.\r\n\r\nThere are four main elements to the myHealth service: Data, Reports, History and Feedback. Each element tries to approach a different issue relating to achieving the patient/doctor relationship set out by Goetz. From a technical stand point, myHealth also explores some of the issues arising when dealing with digital information on different devices, such as smart phones and tablets.', 'myHealth', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '382-revision-2', '', '', '2011-06-30 10:00:26', '2011-06-30 10:00:26', '', 382, 'http://www.adroot.co.uk/portfolio/382-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
